Diagnostic remarks.
A large, green species, with broad tegmina and hind wings slightly surpassing the tegminal apices (
Fig. 30E
). 

A. fasciata

can be distinguished from a similar 

A. tanzanica

by the presence on the metazona of pronotum of a light, often white patch, bordered with a black band (
Fig. 30C
). The face of individuals of this species in the Central Mozambican population is contrastingly darker than the rest of the head (
Fig. 30D
). The male cercus is slightly sinusoidal when seen from the side (
Fig. 31B
) and its apex has a strongly sclerotized dark disc (
Fig. 31C
); styli of the subgenital plate are small but clearly visible (
Fig. 31D
).
